Thanks Thank you to the person who gave this to me but chose to not be mentioned.

Great Version of Sweet, Laser-Focused Scorcher The transportation machine is turned on for this one, and it's a treat to enjoy it in full "surround sound, you-were-there" effect in Charlie Miller's great version. It starts with a Might as Well that’s a pull-out-the-stops promise of things to come; it’s basically Might as Well Levitate, and the band just flies higher and higher from there, with the ecstatic audience along for the rocket ride. (This is an AUD where you can be transported into the audience and still hear the band crystal-clear.) Many high points (Jack Straw, LiG, Estimated, etc), but what an extraordinary StSt > NFA > Black Peter … Jerry is on an inspired high-intensity slow burn that could drill through metal. This is also a show where Donna is pure organic honey. Might as well take a seat in the audience (though I doubt you'll do much sitting ...)

The best show you've never heard This show is easily among the best of Fall '77, if not the best, right along side 11/4 and 12/27 (apologies to 11/5). Though it's grown in popularity here at LMA, it's really a shame this show hasn't received the praise of more canonical shows like 5/8, 6/9, or 9/3/77. It most definitely belongs in the conversation.
An easy listen. Thanks for the good recording! It is an easy, smooth listen with little echo or cave. Solid, tight show too.
A Classic A super sharp show from start to finish. Keith has a harpsichord sound going on very strongly. This is one of my first shows that I had on tape and sort of grew up with it!
